    <p>The updated <italic>Rfamseq</italic> has a broad taxonomic coverage shown in Figure <xref ref-type="fig" rid="F2">2</xref>. The majority of genomes come from Bacteria (â¼60%), while Eukaryotes and Archaea account for 10% and 3% respectively. Twenty seven percent of genomes in the database are from Viruses but only 748 out of 2404 viral genomes had Rfam matches.</p>
    <fig id="F2" orientation="portrait" position="float">
